  "riddle": "1. Track down the career statistics of a pitcher whose name rings a bell in a 1970s baseball tale: how many times did he send batters back to the bench with a strikeout?\n\n2. A team donned in red, competing fiercely in a summer of hits and home runs, stood at what rank within their division's hierarchy during that season?\n\n3. This ballpark's location on 2nd Street awaits — perhaps its altitude is a clue as to the many soaring home runs witnessed there. What number signifies its height above sea level?\n\n4. Alongside the rows of seats and cheers, visitors rate this iconic spot — what score do they bestow upon it in their reviews?\n\n5. Take the height you discovered in clue 3 and the rating from clue 4; what is the absolute difference between them?\n\n6. In a game of yardage conversion, imagine the height of a towering foul pole at 34 meters — how many yards does that measure out to be?\n\n7. Seek out a notable figure who helped shape the pitching staff of a famous baseball club, gone but not forgotten. What was his age when he departed from the world?\n\n8. Delve into the legacy of the player you just uncovered; for the number representing his years, discover how many unique factors lie within that number.\n\n9. From the city of monuments to one of champions, what is the travel duration, in minutes, when venturing from Baltimore to the thriving heart of Boston?\n\n10. Reflect on your journey — with the driving time from clue 9 in hand, how many 1-bits does its binary form reveal?\n\n11. A legend at the plate, he met an untimely end too soon. What age did he reach before the final curtain call?\n\n12. The year 1978 marked yet another chapter for a storied franchise. Which sequential season was it for the Yankees?\n\n13. Now combine the calculated values of clue 6 and clue 10. Then, the journey concludes with: what does the expression, the absolute difference between 37 and 2, reduced modulo 10 yield? The final answer is a single digit.",
